K", "GLOB.JK", "PJAA.JK", "BAIK.JK", "BDKR.JK", "BSIM.JK", "PKPK.JK", "SURE.JK", "STRK.JK", "PTMP.JK", "FITT.JK", "RCCC.JK", "AMAN.JK", "SOTS.JK", "SMGA.JK", "CBRE.JK", "LPIN.JK", "SMLE.JK", "RBMS.JK", "IKAN.JK", "PRIM.JK", "BEER.JK", "MTLA.JK", "TRIO.JK", "PEGE.JK", "INCI.JK", "SEMA.JK", "TNCA.JK", "GTSI.JK", "PEVE.JK", "TRIL.JK", "PNSE.JK", "IOTF.JK", "MRAT.JK", "ARKA.JK", "CHIP.JK", "YELO.JK", "PORT.JK", "MAGP.JK", "HADE.JK", "IBOS.JK", "TIRA.JK", "PSDN.JK", "MAPB.JK", "ASJT.JK", "BIPP.JK", "CTBN.JK", "VOKS.JK", "SONA.JK", "VKTR.JK", "BSML.JK", "RELF.JK", "LMPI.JK", "KBAG.JK", "DEPO.JK", "IPPE.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-23T14:57:08", "title": "PT Pertamina Geothermal Energy becomes first Indonesian company to rank among top 50 global companies in environmental, social, and governance principles."}, {"body": "PT Hartadinata Abadi Tbk (HRta) secured a 3-year bank loan worth IDR 400 billion from PT Bank Rakyat Indonesia Tbk (BBRI) to allocate towards capital expenditure, working capital, and general corporate needs, with an interest rate of Jakarta Interbank Offered Rate 1M+1.8% per annum. This financing facility exceeds 20% of HRta's total equity of IDR 2.20 trillion as of September 2024, and will support the company's ongoing expansion of its retail jewellery stores, which increased from 78 to 85 units in 2023.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 1, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52172/hrta-secures-idr-loan", "sub_sector": ["apparel-luxury-goods", "banks"], "tags": ["Interest Rates", "Debt", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["HRTA.JK", "BBRI.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-23T14:18:38", "title": "PT Hartadinata Abadi secures IDR 400 billion bank loan for capital expenditure and working capital."}, {"body": "Jhon Veter Firdaus Reagen acquired a 5.01% stake in PT Brigit Biofarmaka Teknologi Tbk (BRIG) by purchasing 30.03 million shares, while other investors, including Lee Suharlie, Wempy, and Rudy Susanto, also increased their stakes in PT Megapower Makmur Tbk (MGMP), PT Planet Properindo Jaya Tbk (PPRO), and PT Graha Prima Mentari Tbk (GPMT), respectively. Meanwhile, several investors, including PT Fersindo Nusa Jaya and HSBC-Fund SVS A/C Chengdong Investment Corp-Self, sold shares in PT Buana Lintas Lautan Tbk (BULL), PT Wir Asia Tbk (WIR), and PT Bumi Resources Tbk (BUMI), respectively.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 65, "sector": "infrastructures", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52171/jhon-veter-firdaus-owns-brigit-biofarmaka-obat-shares", "sub_sector": ["utilities", "consumer-services", "food-beverage", "oil-gas-coal", "software-it-services"], "tags": ["Market Trends", "Market Sentiment", "IDX", "Executive Changes", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["MPOW.JK", "PLAN.JK", "GRPM.JK", "BULL.JK", "WIRG.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-23T14:02:44", "title": "Multiple investors, including Jhon Veter Firdaus Reagen, make significant changes to their stakes in various Indonesian companies, including PT Brigit Biofarmaka Teknologi and PT Graha Prima Mentari."}, {"body": "PT Buyung Poetra Sembada Tbk (HOKI) is promoting alternative rice products, such as corn, cassava, and brown rice, under its Dailymeal brand, aiming to position itself as a pioneer in healthy rice in Indonesia. The company has partnered with Indomarco PT Gurih Mitra Perkasa to expand distribution, with a projected transaction value of IDR 130 billion over one year, and has recorded a 19.9% year-on-year sales growth to IDR 1.1 trillion in Q3 2024.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-non-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52170/hoki-readies-cassava-rice-product", "sub_sector": ["food-beverage"], "tags": ["Market Trends", "Earnings Report", "IDX", "Grains", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["HOKI.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-23T13:33:28", "title": "Hoki Strengthens Business with Alternative Rice Products and Distribution Expansion"}, {"body": "PT Indoritel Makmur Internasional Tbk's subsidiary, PT Mega Akses Persada, has secured a financing facility of IDR 5.9 trillion (approximately USD 390 million) from PT Bank Mandiri Tbk and PT Bank Syariah Indonesia Tbk, with a 13-year term and an annual fixed interest rate of 7.50%. The loan will be used to refinance equipment for fibre optic networks, capital expenditures for 2025-2026, and capex budget for 2026-2027, with no material impact on the parent company's financial condition.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 2, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "financials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52164/dnet-secures-financing-bank-mandiri-bsi-whats-allocation-for", "sub_sector": ["holding-investment-companies", "banks", "banks"], "tags": ["Debt", "Interest Rates", "Sharia Economy", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["DNET.JK", "BRIS.JK", "BMRI.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-23T10:19:08", "title": "PT Indoritel Makmur Internasional's subsidiary receives IDR 5.9 trillion financing facility from Bank Mandiri and BSI."}, {"body": "ExxonMobil (XOM) has signed a memorandum of understanding with the Indonesian government to develop carbon capture storage and petrochemical projects, with an initial investment of $10 billion and a long-term total investment estimated at $15 billion. The project, which aims to reduce CO2 emissions by 90%, will include a CCS facility in the Sunda Asri Strait and a petrochemical plant on a 500-hectare site, with the Indonesian government establishing a special task force to expedite the investment's realization.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 2, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "energy", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52163/exxonmobil-invests-carbon-capture-storage-indonesia", "sub_sector": ["oil-gas-coal"], "tags": ["Energy Commodities", "Market Trends", "Fertilizers", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2025-01-23T08:24:41", "title": "ExxonMobil signs deal with Indonesian government to invest up to $15 billion in carbon capture and petrochemical projects."}, {"body": "BYD (BYDDF) will invest $1 billion to build a factory in Subang, West Java, with a production capacity of 150,000 electric cars per year, aiming to complete construction by the end of 2025. The investment will allow BYD to import electric cars to Indonesia without import duties, supporting the government's target of producing 600,000 electric cars domestically by 2030.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 1, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 2, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52162/byd-invests-electric-car-manufacturing-plant-indonesia", "sub_sector": ["automobiles-components"], "tags": ["Market Trends", "Foreign Investor", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2025-01-23T07:07:26", "title": "BYD to Build $1 Billion Electric Car Factory in Indonesia with 150,000 Unit Annual Capacity"}, {"body": "The Indonesian composite stock price index (JCI) closed 1.05% higher at 7,257.13 on Wednesday, driven by strong performances in the technology sector (+2.54%) and top stocks such as PT Amman Mineral Internasional Tbk (AMMN) (+5.52%), PT Telkom Indonesia Tbk (TLKM) (+3.80%), and PT Bank Mandiri Tbk (BMRI) (+1.65%). Foreign investors recorded a net buy of IDR 292.99 billion on Wednesday, but still posted a net sell of IDR 3.05 trillion on an annual basis, indicating mixed capital flow dynamics throughout the year.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "basic-materials", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52161/tech-sector-pushes-jci-property-sector-pressure", "sub_sector": ["basic-materials", "telecommunication", "banks"], "tags": ["IDX Composite", "IDX", "Market Trends", "Foreign Investor", "Market Sentiment", "Bullish"], "tickers": ["AMMN.JK", "TLKM.JK", "BMRI.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-23T06:08:42", "title": "Indonesian Composite Index Closes 1.05% Higher at 7,257.13, Led by Technology Sector and Strong Performances from Top Stocks."}, {"body": "Foreign investors sold a net 697.01 million shares on the Indonesia Stock Exchange, with PT Goto Gojek Tokopedia Tbk (GOTO) leading the sell list with 722.14 million shares, followed by PT Bumi Resources Tbk (BUMI) with 38.11 million shares. On the other hand, PT Telkom Indonesia Tbk (TLKM) saw the largest net buy with 56.12 million shares, followed by PT Buana Lintas Lautan Tbk (BULL) with 40 million shares and PT Sinergi Multi Lestariindo Tbk (SMLE) with 32.25 million shares.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 0, "management": 0, "ownership": 2, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 2, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "technology", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52160/foreign-sales-strong-sell-shares", "sub_sector": ["software-it-services", "oil-gas-coal", "oil-gas-coal", "telecommunication"], "tags": ["IDX", "Foreign Investor", "Market Trends", "Bearish"], "tickers": ["GOTO.JK", "BUMI.JK", "BULL.JK", "TLKM.JK"], "timestamp": "2025-01-22T20:09:39", "title": "Foreign Investors Net Sell 697 Million Shares on Indonesia Stock Exchange"}, {"body": "Fore Coffee, a startup in the food and beverages sector, has opened 217 stores across 43 cities as of September 30, 2024, with 61 new stores launched throughout 2024, driven by its research and development team's deep understanding of the Indonesian coffee market. The company plans to introduce new products and expand to new markets, aiming to capitalize on the high growth potential of the coffee industry, which is projected to reach an average annual growth rate of 11% until 2030.", "dimension": {"dividend": 0, "financials": 0, "future": 2, "management": 0, "ownership": 0, "sustainability": 0, "technical": 0, "valuation": 0}, "score": 75, "sector": "consumer-non-cyclicals", "source": "https://www.idnfinancials.com/news/52159/fore-reveals-recipe-dominate-premium-coffee-market", "sub_sector": ["food-beverage"], "tags": ["Product Launch", "Market Trends", "IDX", "Bullish"], "tickers": [], "timestamp": "2025-01-22T18:13:42", "title": "Fore Coffee Reveals Strategies to Meet Demand for Premium Coffee at Affordable Prices Amid Rapid Expansion."}]